# Styling Conventions

## SCSS
- **Default style language**: SCSS (configured in [angular.json](mdc:angular.json))
- **Global styles**: [styles.scss](mdc:src/styles.scss)
- **Component styles**: Use `styleUrl: './component.scss'` (singular)

## Component Styles
- Keep component styles scoped to the component
- Use `:host` selector for component-level styling
- Avoid global styles in component files

## Style Organization
```scss
// Component SCSS structure
:host {
  // Host element styles
  display: block;
}

.component-wrapper {
  // Container styles
}

.component-element {
  // Element styles
  
  &--modifier {
    // BEM modifier
  }
  
  &:hover {
    // Pseudo-states
  }
}

// Media queries at the end
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  // Responsive styles
}
```

## HTML Templates
- Use Prettier for HTML formatting (configured in [package.json](mdc:package.json))
- Parser is set to "angular" for proper Angular template formatting

## Best Practices
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) for theming
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Keep specificity low
- Use semantic class names
- Avoid inline styles in templates

## Bundle Size Limits
Per [angular.json](mdc:angular.json):
- Component styles warning: 4kB
- Component styles error: 8kB
Keep component styles lean and focused.
